args: La la laaaaa â™ª\nRight then! Our next stop is...
Sure is! I'm just deciding where to\ntake the circus next.
Do you have anywhere specific in mind?
I was considering the village of Hyburn.\nIt's riiiight...oveeeer...here.
Whoa. That's a long way from here.
Looks like you have to cross deserts and\nvolcanoes on the way, too. Are you sure\nyou want to make a journey like that?
That's all the more reason we should go!
No circus has EVER performed there.
I mean, you'd be crazy to even try and\nget there, right?
But that's no reason for those people to\nsuffer a sad, circus-less existence!
If I'm going to fulfill my dream of making\neveryone happy, that means EVERYONE.
Fair enough. But will you at least\nlet me help you out?
You're going to need all the assistance\nyou can get on a journey like this.
N-not now! We need to prepare!
...Okay, is this SERIOUSLY the only way\nwe can get to this Hyburn place?
Uh oh. I think an eruption's coming!
...This forest is so very eerie.\nAre we SURE this is the right way?
So long as the map is right! ...Er, which\nI'm sure it is. Anyway, take a left here.
Out of our way, fiends! Hah!
That was quite impressive, Annelie.\nEven while in the midst of life-and-death\ncombat, you know how to put on a show.
Try this hooded cloak. It'll help protect\nyou from the stormâ€”at least a little.
Wait, don't tell me you brought enough\nfor everyone?
Of course, silly! I knew we had to cross\na desert, after all.
We're almost there, everyone!\nJust a bit longer!
It's amazing how nothing makes her falter.
Hang on a sec. This ain't a village!\nIt's just a big pile of nothin'!
But it's written right here on this map...
Over here, everyone!\nAt the bottom of this cliff!
There's a village at the bottom of a CLIFF?!
We'll never be able to lower the tent\ndown such a sheer incline.
We'll set the tent up here.
The hell good is that gonna do?!
If we can't lower the tent to the folks,\nthen we bring folks to the tent!
And how exactly do we do that?
I'll just fire up Liger's Delivery Service\nand ferry 'em up here!
Have that tent ready by the time\nI get back, okay? Thaaaanks!
She is not listening to reason.\n...Or anything else, for that matter.
I always knew she was a bit of a wild one,\nbut this really tears the sheets.
Well, nothing to do now but get the tent\nready and hope she's all right.
Thank you all so much for coming today!
Thought I'd be lyin' in the cold, cold ground\na'fore I ever got to see a circus.
We NEVER get entertainment out here.\nHow simply delightful!
Sure looks like everyone enjoyed the show.
Yeah. I'm really glad it was a success.\nStill, you must be exhausted after that\nlong journey, right?
Aw, you're sweet to look after meâ€”\nbut I'm fine and dandy!
I'm not sure I could put on a performance\nafter a journey like that. Don't you ever\nfind it... I don't know. Exhausting?
But once I see that happy audience,\nit makes all the fatigue just...poof!
Once I'm on stage, all that matters\nis that everyone has a good time.
No, you are. No matter how much hardship\nyou've been through, you're still able to\nhelp people forget their own cares.
Yeah, but I could say the same about you.
You never shy from a fight, and you've\nhelped more folks than I can count.\nI have nothing but respect for that.
Ma'am? Our guests are ready to\ngo back home now.
Thanks, Fritz. Tell 'em I'll be right there.
...I think she's closer to realizing her\ndream than she knows.
